\details{
\code{\link[=prep_daily_weather]{prep_daily_weather()}} retrieves daily weather from BioSIM
(\code{ClimaticEx_Daily} model) for cells in \code{studyArea}, summarizes by ecoregion
(\code{id}), and pivots to the LANDIS-II Climate Library wide format. Internally
it chains \code{\link[=get_elevation_rast]{get_elevation_rast()}}, \code{\link[=create_locations_df]{create_locations_df()}}, \code{\link[=get_clim_daily]{get_clim_daily()}}
(per batch / per year), and \code{\link[=assemble_climate_library_file]{assemble_climate_library_file()}}. Per-batch /
per-year results are cached as an Arrow CSV dataset under
\code{getOption("landisutils.cache.path")}, partitioned by
\verb{<rcp>_<clim_model>}/\code{YEAR}/\code{BatchID}.

\code{\link[=prep_monthly_weather]{prep_monthly_weather()}} retrieves monthly weather from TerraClim via the
\pkg{climateR} package and summarizes by zone using the \pkg{zonal} package.

\code{\link[=prep_monthly_weather_biosim]{prep_monthly_weather_biosim()}} retrieves monthly weather from BioSIM
(\code{Climatic_Monthly} model) using the same point-batch / Arrow caching
pipeline as \code{\link[=prep_daily_weather]{prep_daily_weather()}}, so cells are co-located with the daily
workflow. Internally it chains \code{\link[=get_elevation_rast]{get_elevation_rast()}}, \code{\link[=create_locations_df]{create_locations_df()}},
\code{\link[=get_clim_monthly]{get_clim_monthly()}} (per batch / per year), and
\code{\link[=assemble_climate_library_file_monthly]{assemble_climate_library_file_monthly()}}. Per-batch / per-year results are
cached as an Arrow CSV dataset under \code{getOption("landisutils.cache.path")},
partitioned by \verb{<rcp>_<clim_model>}/\code{YEAR}/\code{BatchID}.

\code{\link[=prep_monthly_weather_climr]{prep_monthly_weather_climr()}} retrieves monthly weather from
\href{https://github.com/bcgov/climr}{climr}, a ClimateNA-style change-factor
downscaler against a PRISM/DAYMET composite reference grid. Cells come from
the same elevation/point machinery as the BioSIM pipeline
(\code{\link[=get_elevation_rast]{get_elevation_rast()}}, \code{\link[=create_locations_df]{create_locations_df()}}); a single
\code{\link[climr:downscale]{climr::downscale()}} call per year is dispatched via \code{\link[furrr:future_map]{furrr::future_map()}}.
climr maintains its own on-disk cache, configured via
\code{options("climr.cache.path" = ...)}; the wrapper defaults this to a
\verb{climr/} subdirectory of \code{getOption("landisutils.cache.path")} when the
option is unset.
